{
  "texts": [
    "Doctors were anonymised in analysis, but their ophthalmological experience is summarised in S3 Table.",
    "Unsurprisingly, junior doctors (J1-J2) attained lower scores than expert ophthalmologists (E1-E5; t = 7.18, p < 0.01), and ophthalmology trainees (T1-T3; t = 11.18, p < 0.01), illustrated in Fig 1.",
    "Ophthalmology trainees approached expertlevel scores with no significant difference between the groups (t = 1.55, p = 0.18).",
    "None of the other LLMs matched any of the expert ophthalmologists, mean mark of real examination candidates, or FRCOphth Part 2 pass mark.",
    "Expert ophthalmologists agreed that the mock examination was a faithful representation of actual FRCOphth Part 2 Written Examination papers with a mean and median score of 3/5 (range 2-4/5)."
  ]
}